      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUCb531ed282b0f10058b17851a8e1cd1d2"></a>Changing the front phonic wheel sensor
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4966"> </a>Remove the left-hand side instrument panel (<a href="77975.html#DUCc08298b82a73100585b0e07f17a720d2">Removing the panel</a>).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4971"> </a>Remove the front half-fairing (<a href="77985.html#DUC1ccd37182a8810058cfc8ef6d8d608d2">Removing the front half-fairing</a>).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_039003851.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4979"> </a>Disconnect connector (A) of front ABS sensor (1) from main wiring.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4981"> </a>Open all clips retaining front ABS sensor cable (1): refer to tables under Section "<a href="78699.html#DUC690d85c02b1310058c6793c8b30eb8d2">Routing wiring harnesses / hoses</a>" for the base version or under Section "<a href="78701.html#DUCba4d95002b1410058c6b93c8b30eb8d2">Routing wiring harnesses / hoses</a>" for the Pikes Peak, Granturismo or Touring versions.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4990"> </a>Undo the retaining screw (2), and remove front ABS sensor (1) with calibrated sealing washer (3), sliding cable out from cable
            grommet (4).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_007203189.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4995"> </a>Before reassembling, make sure that contact parts between front ABS sensor (1) and its seat are free of damage and perfectly
            clean.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4997"> </a>Install the new front ABS sensor (1) on its seat and start screw (2) in its thread.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4999"> </a>Check air gap between front ABS sensor (1) and front phonic wheel (5) as explained under Section "<a href="78703.html#DUCe19fba082b221005820fd17ffc81d1d2">Adjusting the AIR-GAP of phonic wheel sensor</a>".
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5004"> </a>Tighten screw (2) to a torque of 10 Nm Â±10%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_007503190.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5009"> </a>Connect connector (A) to main wiring.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5011"> </a>Fasten all clips retaining front ABS sensor cable (1): refer to tables under Section "<a href="78699.html#DUC690d85c02b1310058c6793c8b30eb8d2">Routing wiring harnesses / hoses</a>" for the base version or under Section "<a href="78701.html#DUCba4d95002b1410058c6b93c8b30eb8d2">Routing wiring harnesses / hoses</a>" for the Pikes Peak, Granturismo or Touring versions.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_007003188.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5022"> </a>Refit the front half-fairing (<a href="77985.html#DUC1ccd37182a8810058cfc8ef6d8d608d2">Refitting the front half-fairing</a>).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5027"> </a>Refit the left-hand side panel (<a href="77977.html#DUC2fbfd0b02a74100585b5e07f17a720d2">Refitting the panel</a>).
         </div>
      </div>
